          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><date>Novr 3<hi rend="sup">rd</hi>
                                        1852</date>,</p>
                              <p>My Dear Sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">As it so seldom<lb/> falls to my lot, to have the
                                        plea-<lb/>sure of hearing from you, I am<lb/> rather tardy
                                        in applying for<lb/> letters; but there is an old adage<lb/>
                                        and a trite one “Better late than<lb/> never.”</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I use all endeavors<lb/> to circulate your
                                        “Occident” but<lb/> with little success, they would<lb/>
                                        here willingly read them gratis,<lb/> but I do not encourage
                                        such a<lb/> mean system. I have but two<lb/> subscribers.
                                                  <persName>Mr. Phs. Bravo</persName><lb/> and
                                                  <persName>Mr. Harris</persName> both of them
                                        you<lb/> may <sic>advertize</sic> as paid from<lb/>
                                        <date>April</date>, the amount as you advised<lb/> me to be
                                        handed over to <persName>Miss<lb/> Peixotto</persName> say
                                        28/ I <sic>dont</sic> know<lb/> how your accounts stand
                                        with<lb/> each other so I am unable to<lb/> make any
                                        limits.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">A bible was once<lb/> ordered for one
                                                  <persName>Revrd Duncan Campbell</persName><lb/>
                                        were you send two or three</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>for approval, the frequent commu-<lb/>nication I have with the
                                        Christian<lb/> clergy might enable me to dispose<lb/> of
                                        them.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">The books I wish could <lb/>be sent immediately as
                                        I require<lb/> them, let me know the amt &amp;<lb/> I can
                                        remit it for you, the following also have been ordered<lb/>
                                        <persName>Dr. Wise's</persName> work—3 copies<lb/>
                                        <persName>Dr Illowy</persName> on the origin and<lb/>
                                        reasons of the Jewish Ceremonies”<lb/>—if completed—3
                                        copies</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Could you be kind enough<lb/> also at the request
                                        of <persName>Miss Peixotto</persName><lb/> to send say a
                                        couple of dozen<lb/> of her Catechisms for this market<lb/>
                                        you would oblige.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I am so busy or would<lb/> gladly contribute to
                                        your periodical<lb/> in a literary way but I shall<lb/>
                                        endeavor to muster sufficient<lb/> time next
                                        opportunity.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Poor <persName>D. Garfaty's</persName> death<lb/>
                                        shocked us all and you may<lb/> judge the state of his
                                        family on<lb/> the receipt of such lamentable news</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>
                                        <add>תהי נפשו צרורה בצרור החיים</add>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">nothing further to add</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I subscribe myself</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Ever Thine</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">
                                        <persName role="author">A Dehevanto</persName>
                              </p>
                    </body>
